# Sandbox Directory Structure

All game content lives under `sandbox/src/`. **Never** add game logic to `viberanium/`.

## Layout

```
sandbox/src/
├── SandboxApp.tsx          # package entry re-export only
├── catalog/                # declarative data — lists, maps, registries (no spawn logic)
│   ├── assets/             # glTF/texture URL constants
│   ├── animations/         # anim pack + clip name maps (e.g. kaykitMedium)
│   ├── characters/         # SkeletalCharacterDef entries + characterDef.ts types
│   ├── props/              # PropDefinition entries + propDefinition.ts types, PROP_CATALOG
│   ├── levels/             # indexed level seeds, levelFile parse, collectAssetUrls
│   ├── keys/               # GAME_COMPONENT_KEYS, attachment tag maps
│   └── ui/                 # theme tokens (loading colors, etc.)
├── entities/               # factories, components, systems
│   ├── actor/              # shared skeletal spawn pipeline
│   ├── player/             # createPlayer, playerController, input system
│   ├── combat/             # attachCombatActor, equipWeapon, installCombatSystems, death strip
│   ├── enemies/            # robot, combatMech, dummy + testAi
│   └── ground/             # spawnGround — groundPlane entity
├── scenes/
│   └── common/             # createPlayableScene, useLevelScene, prop (re-export instantiateProp)
├── storage/                # levelLocalStore (shared key construct.levelLocalStore)
├── globals/                # bootstrap, sceneManager (session autoloads)
├── menus/                  # performance, levels LevelSelectModal
└── ui/
    ├── app/                # SandboxApp shell
    └── theme/              # style.css + design tokens
```

## Catalog rule

A file belongs in `catalog/` when it is **primarily declarative data** consumed elsewhere:

| Belongs in `catalog/` | Belongs outside `catalog/` |
|-----------------------|----------------------------|
| URL/path constants | `loadSkeletalCharacter`, `spawnActor` |
| `Record<id, Definition>` maps | `installTestAiSystem` |
| Clip name maps | `createPlayer` |
| `SkeletalCharacterDef` instances | Component `createX()` factories |
| `PropDefinition` / `PROP_CATALOG` | Scene `load()` / `unload()` |
| `GAME_COMPONENT_KEYS` | — |
| Level seeds / `levelFile` parse / indexed layouts | — |

`catalog/` may import `catalog/*` and `viberanium` types. **`catalog/` must not import from `entities/`, `scenes/`, or `globals/`.**

Levels use portable indexed `LevelDefinition` from viberanium (re-exported). `.level` authoring JSON is parsed in `levelFile.ts`. `instantiateProp` lives in `viberanium/spawn` — sandbox `scenes/common/prop.ts` re-exports it.

Types live in the same folder as the data or helpers they describe. Do not add a shared `catalog/types/` folder.

Engine `COMPONENT_KEYS` stays in `viberanium`. Sandbox-specific keys live in `catalog/keys/components.ts`.

## Entity rule

| Folder | Role |
|--------|------|
| `entities/actor/` | `loadSkeletalCharacter`, `spawnSkeletalCharacter`, `spawnActor` |
| `entities/player/` | `createPlayer`, player components + `installPlayerInputSystem` |
| `entities/combat/` | `attachCombatActor`, `equipWeapon`, `wireFullBodyClips`, `installCombatSystems`, death strip |
| `entities/enemies/<kind>/` | `createRobot`, `createCombatMech`, … + shared `components/`, `systems/` |

New enemies follow `entities/enemies/spider/` with `createSpider.ts`, `components/`, `systems/`.

## Scenes rule

- `scenes/common/createPlayableScene.ts` — installs scene systems once; `load()` / `unload()` lifecycle (unload must dispose `installSkeletalCharacterSystems`)
- `scenes/common/useLevelScene.ts` — maps indexed `LevelDefinition` + aiPackages → playable scene
- `scenes/common/prop.ts` — re-export engine `instantiateProp`
- `entities/ground/spawnGround.ts` — ground entity with `groundPlane` component

Main menu Load Level opens `menus/levels/LevelSelectModal`; Digit1–4 load `testOne`–`testFour`; each `switchTo` creates a **fresh** scene (never reuse one scene across levels).

## Globals rule

`globals/bootstrap.ts` and `globals/sceneManager.ts` are session composition only — no entity factories, no level spawn data. Bootstrap seeds level local store when empty.

## UI / menus rule

- `ui/app/SandboxApp.tsx` — React shell; imports `globals/bootstrap`
- `menus/` — overlay components (`menus/performance/`, `menus/levels/`)
- Master CSS: `ui/theme/style.css`; feature CSS colocated with components

## Forbidden

- Barrel `index.ts` anywhere under `sandbox/src/`
- `catalog/types/` — colocate types with their catalog folder
- Catalog files with registry writes or `install*System`
- `startup/`, `levels/`, `character/`, `npcs/`, `world/` paths (removed — use structure above)
- Component key strings outside `catalog/keys/` (except `viberanium` `COMPONENT_KEYS`)
- `staticProps.ts` — use engine `instantiateProp` via `scenes/common/prop.ts`
- Importing `construct` from sandbox
